About this item

  • [FOLDABLE & SOFT MEMORY FOAM PADDING]: Features flexible headphones with telescopic arms and soft ear pads. The headphones fold inside the arm, making them perfect for easy storage and travelling.
  • [COMFORTABLE LIGHTWEIGHT DESIGN]: Comfortable for kids and adults alike, the soft memory foam ear cushions are extremely lightweight, allowing for up to 8 hours usage without excess pressure build up, meaning you won't feel any discomfort even after many hours of gaming. The overall weight is only 0.66lb; approximately 40% lighter than standard gaming headsets.
  • [NOISE CANCELLING ANTI-STATIC MICROPHONE]: The bendable microphone arm can be fixed to any position to ensure the clearest voice pick-up, and filters out surrounding environmental noise and eliminates static. The Senzer SG500 noise cancelling headset with microphone provides real-time in game chat without delay, making it easier to communicate with team-mates, friends and family without unnecessary interruptions.
  • [SURROUND SOUND CAPABLE]: Proven to enhance your gaming performance, this surround sound gaming headset gives you crystal clear audio and provides you a truly immersive video game experience. Pick up the direction of gunfire, vehicles and voices more clearly, as well as enjoying a more enhanced audio experience as subtle sounds like footsteps, wind and rain are projected with more clarity and precision.
  • [PLUG AND PLAY MULTI-PLATFORM COMPATIBILITY]: Works with most modern devices which include a 3.5mm jack like PlayStation 4, Xbox One (Older version requires adaptor), Apple Mac, Laptop, PC & Mobile. No drivers or downloads required, simply Plug & Play, making it the ideal headset for travelling or as a gift, safe in the knowledge it will fit a multitude of devices.

SENZER-Fully immerse yourself in your gaming environment

Why choose the Senzer Gaming Headset?

  • Clear voice projection. Blocks out background sounds with noise cancelling anti-static microphone.
  • Space-saving foldable design. Simply fold the earphones inside the arm, making the headphones compact, easy to store and travel with.
  • Lightweight design, eases pressure on ears and head, allowing for longer gaming time without discomfort.

Soft Padded Headband：

The headband padded with thickened soft foam, reduces pressure on your head. You won't feel any uncomfortable on your head even after a long gaming session.

Soft High Protine Ear Muffs:

Padded with slow rebound memory foam and covers soft high protein ear pads bring you a perfect and comfortable gaming experience even for long time gaming.

Vivid Stereo Surround Sound：

With a surround sound chip, you can experience enhanced in-game sounds from subtle footsteps to thundering explosions, and enjoy accurate enemy positioning for a clear competitive edge when gaming.

Ergonomic Design for All-Day Comfort：

To fit different size of heads,and for a more compact covering feelingto your ears, The headband can be adjusted in several ways to reach the most comfortable fit.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    SAUL ABREU
    5.0 out of 5 stars Now I can record my classes and enjoy my music!
    Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
    Color: BlackVerified Purchase
    I don't normally give reviews of the products that I buy. However, these headphones have surprised me and to fair I think I have to do it.
    I want to clarify that I am very annoying when buying something. I read different reviews, I watch a lot of videos on Youtube to compare products and get an idea of how it works and also know the pros and cons.
    I was looking for a product that wasn't that expensive, but wasn't really cheap either. So at AMAZON's suggestion, I stumbled upon the SENZER SG500. I immediately started researching and followed my pre-purchase protocol. I read the reviews, looked up its features, and apparently the product had everything I was looking for. After careful consideration, I decided to give the SENZER SG500 a try and I must say I have no regrets.
    After a couple of weeks of wearing the SENZER SG500 every day, here are my comments.
    I usually teach online so I needed a product that wouldn't kill my ears (Yes, I have big ears) after two or three hours and the ear pads are so well designed you don't even notice them. They're soft and they adapt themselves to the shape of your head, but more importantly, after a couple of hours, your ears thank you for how great they feel.
    The weight is another thing that surprises me, they are very light and sometimes you forget that you are using them.
    The cable is very well designed. It has a coating made of some kind of sintetic cloth, which is very difficult to break.
    Integrated into the cable, we find a small device that allows you to control both the volume and mute the microphone. And this is appreciated by me, because sometimes you just want to mute the microphone without having to do it on the device you are using (my laptop).
    And speaking of the microphone, it captures the sound with great quality. My students listen to me without problems and I can tell the difference in the new audios and tutorials that I recorded in the last days from the previous ones.
    I am aware that we are talking about a product that is designed for gaming, but this product can be used in other environments, such as a virtual classroom, video calls, recording, and even listening to music. As for the latter, I think it was what surprised me the most. It has such a clear sound that sometimes you think that the music is coming from outside and not from the SENZER SG500 itself. The basses are incredible and is never distorted. Always loud and clear. And I'm used to listening to music with good quality equipment, because sometimes I work at a local radio station with a friend.
    Another aspect that I like is that they can be folded and are easy to transport.
    If I had to describe my overall experience with the SENZER SG500, I have to give them a 5/5. At least in my case and two weeks using the product, it meets all my expectations.
    If you ask me about something negative and I don't know whether to call it a negative, it has to be that I tried the product on my cell phone and although it is true that they sound quite good, the volume is low compared to when I use them on my laptop. I can attribute it to the fact that the sound output from my cell phone is not of quality or that it does not have the correct power to really exploit the potential of the SENZER SG500. But that's probably my phone. Now if you're going to use them for what they were designed for, you won't regret it.
